==Etymology==
Akin to Greek ''-ikos'', English ''-ish'', German ''-isch'', and various suffixes in other Indo-European languages.

==Latin==
===Adjective Suffix===
'''-icus''' ''m'', '''[[-ica]]''' ''f'', '''[[-icum]]''' ''n''

# of or pertaining to; adjective suffix appended to various words to turn them into adjectives.

